From ce58abee92377cf5aef12aff93eca7adb7be25d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Raghavendran Madhavan <raghmadh@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Jul 2025 18:57:04 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PLATFORM:wifi: ath12k: Update ath12k reference segements
 in Minidump

Updating the following related to minidump functionality

- Updated compile time flag CPTCFG_ATHDEBUG for Minidump unregister
	If CPTCFG_ATHDEBUG flag is enabled then unregister flow shoul
happen as part for core deinit.

- Updated Minidump write Fops to remove the '\n' char entries.
	When user gives input to a sysfs entry, remove the unwanted
strings before using them.

- Added STUB functions for Minidump functions.
	When CONFIG_QCA_MINIDUMP is enabled and CPTCFG_MAC80211_ATHMEMDEBUG
is disabled, minidump functionality is enabled.

Signed-off-by: Raghavendran Madhavan <raghmadh@qti.qualcomm.com>
